Structs/AstronomySpecialType.html#/s:6li.name: type
Structs/AstronomySpecialType.html#/s:6li.abstract: Indicates if the sun is up or down all day.

Structs/AstronomyObjectType.html#/s:6lib.name: events
Structs/AstronomyObjectType.html#/s:6lib.abstract: Lists all sunrise/sunset events during the day.

Structs/AstronomyObjectType.html#/s:6lib.name: name
Structs/AstronomyObjectType.html#/s:6lib.abstract: Object name. Currently, the sun is the only supported astronomical object.

Structs/AstronomyObjectType.html#/s:6lib.name: special
Structs/AstronomyObjectType.html#/s:6lib.abstract: This element is only present if there are no astronomical events. In this case it will indicate if the sun is up or down the whole day.

Structs/AstronomyEventType.html#/s:6libt.name: hour
Structs/AstronomyEventType.html#/s:6libt.abstract: Hour at which the event is happening (local time).

Structs/AstronomyEventType.html#/s:6libt.name: minute
Structs/AstronomyEventType.html#/s:6libt.abstract: Minute at which the event is happening (local time).

Structs/AstronomyEventType.html#/s:6libt.name: type
Structs/AstronomyEventType.html#/s:6libt.abstract: Indicates the type of the event. Returns either rise or set

Structs/HolidayTypes.html#/s:6libtad12Ho.name: htDefault
Structs/HolidayTypes.html#/s:6libtad12Ho.abstract: Default holiday set: federal, federallocal, obs1, weekday.

Structs/HolidayTypes.html#/s:6libtad12Ho.name: religious
Structs/HolidayTypes.html#/s:6libtad12Ho.abstract: All religious holidays: buddhism, christian, hebrew, hinduism, muslim, orthodox.

Structs/HolidayTypes.html#/s:6libtad12Ho.name: otherreligion
Structs/HolidayTypes.html#/s:6libtad12Ho.abstract: Religious holidays, not covered by other types.

Structs/HolidayTypes.html#/s:6libtad12Ho.name: defacto
Structs/HolidayTypes.html#/s:6libtad12Ho.abstract: Some countries (e.g. Sweden) have days which are de facto treted as official holidays, even if there’s no legal regulation.

Structs/HolidayTypes.html#/s:6libtad12Ho.name: halfday
Structs/HolidayTypes.html#/s:6libtad12Ho.abstract: Half day holidays (only afternoon off). These days can be half day holidays either by law, or being de facto half day holidays (e.g. Sweden).

Structs/HolidayStateType.html#/s:6libtad.name: iso
Structs/HolidayStateType.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: An ISO 3166-1 country or ISO 3166-2 country state code (see [ISO3166]).

Structs/HolidayStateType.html#/s:6libtad.name: exception
Structs/HolidayStateType.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: Eventual exception if the holiday does not affect the whole state/subdivision.

Structs/DstEntryType.html#/s:6libtad12Ds.name: region
Structs/DstEntryType.html#/s:6libtad12Ds.abstract: The geographical region where this information is valid. Contains country, a textual description of the region and the name of the biggest place.

Structs/DstEntryType.html#/s:6libtad12Ds.name: stdtimezone
Structs/DstEntryType.html#/s:6libtad12Ds.abstract: Information about the standard time zone. This element is always returned.

Structs/DstEntryType.html#/s:6libtad12Ds.name: dsttimezone
Structs/DstEntryType.html#/s:6libtad12Ds.abstract: Information about the daylight savings time zone. Suppressed, if there are no DST changes in the queried year.

Structs/DstEntryType.html#/s:6libtad12Ds.name: dstend
Structs/DstEntryType.html#/s:6libtad12Ds.abstract: Ending date of daylight savings time. Suppressed, if there are no DST changes in the queried year.

Structs/DstEntryType.html#/s:6libtad12Ds.name: dststart
Structs/DstEntryType.html#/s:6libtad12Ds.abstract: Starting date of daylight savings time. Suppressed, if there are no DST changes in the queried year.

Structs/DstEntryType.html#/s:6libtad12Ds.name: timechanges
Structs/DstEntryType.html#/s:6libtad12Ds.abstract: Time changes (daylight savings time). Only present if requested and information is available.

Structs/DSTListRegion.html#/s:6libtad13D.name: biggestplace
Structs/DSTListRegion.html#/s:6libtad13D.abstract: Name of the biggest city within the region

Structs/DSTListRegion.html#/s:6libtad13D.name: locations
Structs/DSTListRegion.html#/s:6libtad13D.abstract: A list of all locations referenced by this region. Only returned if requested by specifying the parameter listplaces.

Structs/DSTListLocation.html#/s:6libtad1.name: state
Structs/DSTListLocation.html#/s:6libtad1.abstract: The state of the location within the country (only if applicable).

Structs/DSTEntrySpecialType.html#/s:6lib.name: type
Structs/DSTEntrySpecialType.html#/s:6lib.abstract: Indicates if the region does not observe DST at all, or is on DST all year long.

Structs/WeekdaysType.html#/s:6libtad12We.name: count
Structs/WeekdaysType.html#/s:6libtad12We.abstract: How many days in total have been counted.

Structs/WeekdaysType.html#/s:6libtad12We.name: type
Structs/WeekdaysType.html#/s:6libtad12We.abstract: Specifies whether or not the weekdays counted were part of an included or excluded filter.

Structs/VerboseTimeChangeType.html#/s:6l.name: newlocaltime
Structs/VerboseTimeChangeType.html#/s:6l.abstract: Local time after transition, split up into components.

Structs/VerboseTimeChangeType.html#/s:6l.name: oldlocaltime
Structs/VerboseTimeChangeType.html#/s:6l.abstract: Local time after transition, split up into components.

Structs/VerboseTimeChangeType.html#/s:6l.name: utctime
Structs/VerboseTimeChangeType.html#/s:6l.abstract: Time stamp of transition in UTC time, split up into components.

Structs/Utc.html#/s:6libtad3UtcV4timeAA8.name: time
Structs/Utc.html#/s:6libtad3UtcV4timeAA8.abstract: UTC time stamp in ISO8601 format, and (if requested) split into components.

Structs/Timechange.html#/s:6libtad10Time.name: newdst
Structs/Timechange.html#/s:6libtad10Time.abstract: New DST offset in seconds. Value will be null/empty if there is no DST for this location.

Structs/Timechange.html#/s:6libtad10Time.name: newlocaltime
Structs/Timechange.html#/s:6libtad10Time.abstract: Local time after transition, formatted as ISO 8601 (see [ISO8601]) time.

Structs/Timechange.html#/s:6libtad10Time.name: newoffset
Structs/Timechange.html#/s:6libtad10Time.abstract: New total offset to UTC in seconds.

Structs/Timechange.html#/s:6libtad10Time.name: newzone
Structs/Timechange.html#/s:6libtad10Time.abstract: New time zone offset to UTC in seconds if there is a time zone change for this place. Otherwise the value will be null/empty. Time zones changes happen only very rarely, so the field will be null/empty on most occasions.

Structs/Timechange.html#/s:6libtad10Time.name: oldlocaltime
Structs/Timechange.html#/s:6libtad10Time.abstract: Local time after transition, formatted as ISO 8601 (see [ISO8601]) time.

Structs/Timechange.html#/s:6libtad10Time.name: utctime
Structs/Timechange.html#/s:6libtad10Time.abstract: Time stamp of transition in UTC time, formatted as ISO 8601 (see [ISO8601]) time.

Structs/TimeZoneType.html#/s:6libtad12Ti.name: offset
Structs/TimeZoneType.html#/s:6libtad12Ti.abstract: The time zone offset (from UTC) in string representation.

Structs/TimeZoneType.html#/s:6libtad12Ti.name: zonedst
Structs/TimeZoneType.html#/s:6libtad12Ti.abstract: DST component of time zone offset in seconds.

Structs/TimeZoneType.html#/s:6libtad12Ti.name: zoneoffset
Structs/TimeZoneType.html#/s:6libtad12Ti.abstract: Basic time zone offset (without DST) in seconds.

Structs/TimeType.html#/s:6libtad8TimeTyp.name: datetime
Structs/TimeType.html#/s:6libtad8TimeTyp.abstract: Date and time, split up into components. The element is only present, if the verbosetime parameter is set to 1.

Structs/TimeType.html#/s:6libtad8TimeTyp.name: iso
Structs/TimeType.html#/s:6libtad8TimeTyp.abstract: ISO representation of date and time, time zone included (see [ISO8601]) if different from UTC. If time is not applicable, only the date is shown.

Structs/TimeType.html#/s:6libtad8TimeTyp.name: timezone
Structs/TimeType.html#/s:6libtad8TimeTyp.abstract: Timezone information. Element is only present if different from UTC and requested by the caller (parameter tz).

Structs/Period.html#/s:6libtad6PeriodV12.name: calendardays
Structs/Period.html#/s:6libtad6PeriodV12.abstract: Number of calendar days in calculated period.

Structs/Period.html#/s:6libtad6PeriodV11.name: skippeddays
Structs/Period.html#/s:6libtad6PeriodV11.abstract: Number of days which was skipped in the calculated period.

Structs/Period.html#/s:6libtad6PeriodV8h.name: holidays
Structs/Period.html#/s:6libtad6PeriodV8h.abstract: Holidays which occur in the requested period.

Structs/Period.html#/s:6libtad6PeriodV8w.name: weekdays
Structs/Period.html#/s:6libtad6PeriodV8w.abstract: The spread of excluded or included weekdays in includeddays.

Structs/LocationType.html#/s:6libtad12Lo.name: matchparam
Structs/LocationType.html#/s:6libtad12Lo.abstract: The part of the queried placeid that this location matches. Only for the timeservice.

Structs/LocationType.html#/s:6libtad12Lo.name: time
Structs/LocationType.html#/s:6libtad12Lo.abstract: Time information about the location. Only present if requested.

Structs/LocationType.html#/s:6libtad12Lo.name: timechanges
Structs/LocationType.html#/s:6libtad12Lo.abstract: Time changes (daylight savings time). Only present if requested and information is available.

Structs/LocationType.html#/s:6libtad12Lo.name: astronomy
Structs/LocationType.html#/s:6libtad12Lo.abstract: Astronomical information – sunrise and sunset times. Only for the timeservice and if requested.

Structs/LocationAstroType.html#/s:6libta.name: matchparam
Structs/LocationAstroType.html#/s:6libta.abstract: The part of the queried placeid that this location matches.

Structs/HolidayType.html#/s:6libtad11Hol.name: id
Structs/HolidayType.html#/s:6libtad11Hol.abstract: Identifier for the holiday definition. Please note that this id is not unique, not even with a single year – the same holiday event may be returned multiple time because it is observed on a different day, or because it is scheduled in a different calendar (Hebrew or Muslim calendar) and happens multiple times within a Gregorian year. Use the uid field for purposes where you need a unique identifier.

Structs/HolidayType.html#/s:6libtad11Hol.name: uid
Structs/HolidayType.html#/s:6libtad11Hol.abstract: Id for the shown holiday instance. The id is designed to be unique across all holiday instances generated by the timeanddate.com API services and respects different calendars and other reasons that may cause events to occurs multiple times within one Gregorian year.

Structs/HolidayType.html#/s:6libtad11Hol.name: date
Structs/HolidayType.html#/s:6libtad11Hol.abstract: Date/time of the holiday instance. Most holidays do not have a specific time – in this case the time components will be skipped. Some special events like equinoxes and solstices include the exact time of the event as well, in this case the timestamp will be in local time zone (including time zone data) (countries with multiple time zones: local time in capital city).

Structs/HolidayType.html#/s:6libtad11Hol.name: country
Structs/HolidayType.html#/s:6libtad11Hol.abstract: Country of the holiday instance. This element is not present in businessdate and businessduration services.

Structs/HolidayType.html#/s:6libtad11Hol.name: locations
Structs/HolidayType.html#/s:6libtad11Hol.abstract: Summary of locations where this holiday instance is valid. This element is not present in businessdate and businessduration services, and only present if the holiday instance does not affect the whole country.

Structs/HolidayType.html#/s:6libtad11Hol.name: states
Structs/HolidayType.html#/s:6libtad11Hol.abstract: States/subdivisions that are affected by this holiday instance. This element is not present in businessdate and businessduration services, and only present if the holiday instance is not valid in the whole country.

Structs/HolidayType.html#/s:6libtad11Hol.name: oneliner
Structs/HolidayType.html#/s:6libtad11Hol.abstract: A short description of the holiday instance. This element is not present in businessdate and businessduration services.

Structs/HolidayType.html#/s:6libtad11Hol.name: types
Structs/HolidayType.html#/s:6libtad11Hol.abstract: Classification of the holiday. Most days have only one classification, bust some have multiple types associated. This happens e.g. in conjunction with religious days that also are flag days. This element is not present in businessdate and businessduration services.

Structs/HolidayType.html#/s:6libtad11Hol.name: url
Structs/HolidayType.html#/s:6libtad11Hol.abstract: Further information about the specific holiday. The URL points to the timeanddate.com web page.

Structs/BusinessHolidayType.html#/s:6lib.name: count
Structs/BusinessHolidayType.html#/s:6lib.abstract: The number of holidays in the results.

Structs/BusinessHolidayType.html#/s:6lib.name: list
Structs/BusinessHolidayType.html#/s:6lib.abstract: Holidays which occur in the requested period.

Structs/BusinessHolidayType.html#/s:6lib.name: type
Structs/BusinessHolidayType.html#/s:6lib.abstract: Either included or excluded, specifying whether or not the holidays in the result array were included or excluded when queried.

Structs/AstronomyObjectDetailsType.html#.name: current
Structs/AstronomyObjectDetailsType.html#.abstract: The current data for the object. Only if requested. (Astronomy)

Structs/AstronomyObjectDetailsType.html#.name: result
Structs/AstronomyObjectDetailsType.html#.abstract: The specific data for the object at isotime/utctime.. (Astrodata)

Structs/AstronomyObjectDetailsType.html#.name: days
Structs/AstronomyObjectDetailsType.html#.abstract: Lists and wraps all requested days where events are happening. (Astronomy)

Structs/AstronomyDayEvent.html#/s:6libta.name: altitude
Structs/AstronomyDayEvent.html#/s:6libta.abstract: Altitude of the center of the queried astronomical object above an ideal horizon. Only for meridian type events.

Structs/AstronomyDayEvent.html#/s:6libta.name: azimuth
Structs/AstronomyDayEvent.html#/s:6libta.abstract: Horizontal direction of the astronomical object at set/rise time (referring to true north). North is 0 degrees, east is 90 degrees, south is 180 degrees and west is 270 degrees. Only for rise and set type events.

Structs/AstronomyDayEvent.html#/s:6libta.name: distance
Structs/AstronomyDayEvent.html#/s:6libta.abstract: Distance of the earth’s center to the center of the queried astronomical object in kilometers. Only for meridian type events.

Structs/AstronomyDayEvent.html#/s:6libta.name: isotime
Structs/AstronomyDayEvent.html#/s:6libta.abstract: Local time at which the event is happening in ISO 8601 format (including UTC offset). Only returned if requested by specifying the parameter isotime.

Structs/AstronomyDayEvent.html#/s:6libta.name: utctime
Structs/AstronomyDayEvent.html#/s:6libta.abstract: UTC time at which the event is happening in ISO 8601 format. Only returned if requested by specifying the parameter utctime.

Structs/AstronomyDayEvent.html#/s:6libta.name: illuminated
Structs/AstronomyDayEvent.html#/s:6libta.abstract: The fraction of the Moon’s surface illuminated by the Sun’s rays as seen from the selected location. Only for the moon for meridian type events.

Structs/AstronomyDayEvent.html#/s:6libta.name: posangle
Structs/AstronomyDayEvent.html#/s:6libta.abstract: The counterclockwise angle of the midpoint of the Moon’s bright limb as seen from the selected location. Only for the moon for meridian type events.

Structs/AstronomyDay.html#/s:6libtad12As.name: daylength
Structs/AstronomyDay.html#/s:6libtad12As.abstract: Length of this day (time between sunrise and sunset). If the sun is not up on this day, 00:00:00 will reported. If the sun does not set on this day, the value will read 24:00:00.

Structs/AstronomyDay.html#/s:6libtad12As.name: moonphase
Structs/AstronomyDay.html#/s:6libtad12As.abstract: Moon phase for the day. Only if requested.

Structs/AstronomyCurrent.html#/s:6libtad.name: isotime
Structs/AstronomyCurrent.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: Local time stamp for the data in ISO 8601 format (including UTC offset).

Structs/AstronomyCurrent.html#/s:6libtad.name: utctime
Structs/AstronomyCurrent.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: UTC time stamp for the data in ISO 8601 format.

Structs/AstronomyCurrent.html#/s:6libtad.name: altitude
Structs/AstronomyCurrent.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: Altitude of the center of the queried astronomical object above an ideal horizon.

Structs/AstronomyCurrent.html#/s:6libtad.name: azimuth
Structs/AstronomyCurrent.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: Horizontal direction of the astronomical object at set/rise time (referring to true north). North is 0 degrees, east is 90 degrees, south is 180 degrees and west is 270 degrees.

Structs/AstronomyCurrent.html#/s:6libtad.name: distance
Structs/AstronomyCurrent.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: Distance of the earth’s center to the center of the queried astronomical object in kilometers.

Structs/AstronomyCurrent.html#/s:6libtad.name: illuminated
Structs/AstronomyCurrent.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: The fraction of the Moon’s surface illuminated by the Sun’s rays as seen from the selected location. Only for the moon for meridian type events.

Structs/AstronomyCurrent.html#/s:6libtad.name: posangle
Structs/AstronomyCurrent.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: The counterclockwise angle of the midpoint of the Moon’s bright limb as seen from the selected location. Only available for the moon object.

Structs/AstronomyCurrent.html#/s:6libtad.name: moonphase
Structs/AstronomyCurrent.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: The current phase of the moon. Only available for the moon object.

Enums/BussinesDaysFilterType.html#/s:6li.name: all
Enums/BussinesDaysFilterType.html#/s:6li.abstract: Include everything (only supported if include parameter is set to 1).

Enums/BussinesDaysFilterType.html#/s:6li.name: weekendholidays
Enums/BussinesDaysFilterType.html#/s:6li.abstract: Include or exclude weekends and holidays combined.

Enums/BusinessDaysOperatorType.html#/s:6.name: add
Enums/BusinessDaysOperatorType.html#/s:6.abstract: Uses the number specified in parameter to add the days from a start date.

Enums/BusinessDaysOperatorType.html#/s:6.name: subtract
Enums/BusinessDaysOperatorType.html#/s:6.abstract: Uses the number specified in parameter to subtract the days from a start date.

Enums/EventClass.html#/s:6libtad10EventC.name: current
Enums/EventClass.html#/s:6libtad10EventC.abstract: The current phase for the place requested. Additional attributes for illumination (moon), azimuth, distance.

Enums/EventClass.html#/s:6libtad10EventC.name: daylength
Enums/EventClass.html#/s:6libtad10EventC.abstract: Day length. Day length is not reported as an event, but as a separate attribute.

Enums/EventClass.html#/s:6libtad10EventC.name: meridian
Enums/EventClass.html#/s:6libtad10EventC.abstract: Meridian (Noon, highest point) and Anti-Meridian (lowest point) events.

Enums/EventClass.html#/s:6libtad10EventC.name: phase
Enums/EventClass.html#/s:6libtad10EventC.abstract: Moon phase events. Additionally to the phase events (only occurring on four days per lunar month), an additional attribute for the current moon phase is reported for every day.

Enums/EventClass.html#/s:6libtad10EventC.name: setrise
Enums/EventClass.html#/s:6libtad10EventC.abstract: Set and rise events. Event times take atmospheric refraction into account.

Classes/TimeRequest.html#/s:6libtad11Tim.name: placeId
Classes/TimeRequest.html#/s:6libtad11Tim.abstract: Specify the ID of the location you would like to get the current time from. To retrieve the time for multiple places, the corresponding IDs can either be specified as a comma separated list, or by supplying the parameter multiple times (or any combination). There is a limit of maximum 25 locations per requests.

Classes/TimeRequest.html#/s:6libtad11Tim.name: qLimit
Classes/TimeRequest.html#/s:6libtad11Tim.abstract: Maximum number of query results to be returned. This number may be further limited by access key specific restrictions.

Classes/TimeRequest.html#/s:6libtad11Tim.name: geo
Classes/TimeRequest.html#/s:6libtad11Tim.abstract: Return longitude and latitude for the geo object.

Classes/TimeRequest.html#/s:6libtad11Tim.name: lang
Classes/TimeRequest.html#/s:6libtad11Tim.abstract: The preferred language for the esponses. An error will be raised if the language code cannot be recognized. In case the text for a specific event cannot be retrieved in the requested language it will be returned in English instead. This is also the default language.

Classes/TimeRequest.html#/s:6libtad11Tim.name: radius
Classes/TimeRequest.html#/s:6libtad11Tim.abstract: Search radius for translating coordinates (parameter placeid) to locations. Coordinates that could not be translated will yield results for the actual geographical position.

Classes/TimeRequest.html#/s:6libtad11Tim.name: sun
Classes/TimeRequest.html#/s:6libtad11Tim.abstract: Controls if the astronomy element with information about sunrise and sunset shall be added to the result.

Classes/TimeRequest.html#/s:6libtad11Tim.name: time
Classes/TimeRequest.html#/s:6libtad11Tim.abstract: Adds current time under the location object.

Classes/TimeRequest.html#/s:6libtad11Tim.name: timechanges
Classes/TimeRequest.html#/s:6libtad11Tim.abstract: Add a list of time changes during the year to the location object. This listing e.g. shows changes caused by daylight savings time.

Classes/TimeRequest.html#/s:6libtad11Tim.name: tz
Classes/TimeRequest.html#/s:6libtad11Tim.abstract: Add time zone information under the time object.

Classes/TimeRequest.html#/s:6libtad11Tim.name: verbosetime
Classes/TimeRequest.html#/s:6libtad11Tim.abstract: Adds verbose time specification to all ISO 8601 time stamps.

Classes/TimeResponse.html#/s:6libtad12Ti.name: locations
Classes/TimeResponse.html#/s:6libtad12Ti.abstract: This element contains the response data. Iit is modeled as an array of objects with the same content.

Classes/PlacesRequest.html#/s:6libtad13P.name: geo
Classes/PlacesRequest.html#/s:6libtad13P.abstract: Return longitude and latitude for the geo object.

Classes/PlacesRequest.html#/s:6libtad13P.name: lang
Classes/PlacesRequest.html#/s:6libtad13P.abstract: The preferred language for the texts. An error will be raised if the language code cannot be recognized. In case the text for a specific event cannot be retrieved in the requested language it will be returned in English instead. This is also the default language.

Classes/PlacesResponse.html#/s:6libtad14.name: places
Classes/PlacesResponse.html#/s:6libtad14.abstract: This element contains a list of all currently known places, their identifiers and their geographical location (if requested).

Classes/HolidaysResponse.html#/s:6libtad.name: holidays
Classes/HolidaysResponse.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: This element will contain a list of all holiday events within the requested year. If service was queried with calform=full it will also contain an element for every day of the year.

Classes/HolidaysRequest.html#/s:6libtad1.name: country
Classes/HolidaysRequest.html#/s:6libtad1.abstract: Specify the country for which you would like to retrieve the list of holidays. A states ISO code can also be used when applicable (see a countrys state support on Holidays by Country)

Classes/HolidaysRequest.html#/s:6libtad1.name: year
Classes/HolidaysRequest.html#/s:6libtad1.abstract: The year for which the holidays should be retrieved.

Classes/HolidaysRequest.html#/s:6libtad1.name: lang
Classes/HolidaysRequest.html#/s:6libtad1.abstract: The preferred language(s) for the texts. An error will be raised if the language code cannot be recognized. In case the text for a specific event cannot be retrieved in any of the requested languages it will be returned in English instead. To query for multiple languages, specify them as comma separated list or repeat the parameter multiple times. In case a requested translation is not available, it will be omitted from the output.

Classes/HolidaysRequest.html#/s:6libtad1.name: includeTypes
Classes/HolidaysRequest.html#/s:6libtad1.abstract: Holiday types which should be returned. To combine multiple types, either separate them with commas or repeat the parameter with a different value. A negation can be expressed by prefixing the value with a tilde (~) character. Values are combined in the order they are supplied.

Classes/HolidaysRequest.html#/s:6libtad1.name: tz
Classes/HolidaysRequest.html#/s:6libtad1.abstract: Add time zone information under the date object.

Classes/HolidaysRequest.html#/s:6libtad1.name: verbosetime
Classes/HolidaysRequest.html#/s:6libtad1.abstract: AAdds verbose time specification to all ISO 8601 time stamps.

Classes/DSTListResponse.html#/s:6libtad1.name: dstlist
Classes/DSTListResponse.html#/s:6libtad1.abstract: The DST information for each country or region.

Classes/DSTListRequest.html#/s:6libtad14.name: year
Classes/DSTListRequest.html#/s:6libtad14.abstract: The year you want to retrieve the information for.

Classes/DSTListRequest.html#/s:6libtad14.name: country
Classes/DSTListRequest.html#/s:6libtad14.abstract: Specify the country for which you want to retrieve information for in as an ISO3166-1-alpha-2 country code. If unspecified, information for all countries will be returned.

Classes/DSTListRequest.html#/s:6libtad14.name: onlyDST
Classes/DSTListRequest.html#/s:6libtad14.abstract: Return only countries which actually observe DST in the queried year. Other countries will be suppressed.

Classes/DSTListRequest.html#/s:6libtad14.name: lang
Classes/DSTListRequest.html#/s:6libtad14.abstract: The preferred language for the texts. An error will be raised if the language code cannot be recognized. In case the text for a specific event cannot be retrieved in the requested language it will be returned in English instead. This is also the default language.

Classes/DSTListRequest.html#/s:6libtad14.name: listPlaces
Classes/DSTListRequest.html#/s:6libtad14.abstract: For every time zone/country, list the individual places that belong to each record.

Classes/DSTListRequest.html#/s:6libtad14.name: timeChanges
Classes/DSTListRequest.html#/s:6libtad14.abstract: Add a list of time changes during the year to the dstentry object. This listing e.g. shows changes caused by daylight savings time.

Classes/DSTListRequest.html#/s:6libtad14.name: verbosetime
Classes/DSTListRequest.html#/s:6libtad14.abstract: Adds verbose time specification to all ISO 8601 time stamps.

Classes/ConvertTimeResponse.html#/s:6lib.name: locations
Classes/ConvertTimeResponse.html#/s:6lib.abstract: This element contains the time information for the locations in the request. For the XML format, it will be repeated multiple times, while for JSON, it is modeled as an array of objects with the same content.

Classes/ConvertTimeRequest.html#/s:6libt.name: fromPlaceId
Classes/ConvertTimeRequest.html#/s:6libt.abstract: Specify the ID of the location for which the supplied time stamp corresponds. If the time stamp is in UTC, use the location id 1440 (or /utc).

Classes/ConvertTimeRequest.html#/s:6libt.name: toPlaceId
Classes/ConvertTimeRequest.html#/s:6libt.abstract: Specify the ID of the location(s) for which the time stamp should be converted. You can supply multiple locations by either providing them as comma separated list, or by repeating the parameter multiple times. There is a limit of maximum 25 locations per requests.

Classes/ConvertTimeRequest.html#/s:6libt.name: lang
Classes/ConvertTimeRequest.html#/s:6libt.abstract: The preferred language for the texts. An error will be raised if the language code cannot be recognized. In case the text for a specific event cannot be retrieved in the requested language it will be returned in English instead. This is also the default language.

Classes/ConvertTimeRequest.html#/s:6libt.name: radius
Classes/ConvertTimeRequest.html#/s:6libt.abstract: Search radius for translating coordinates (parameter placeid) to locations. Coordinates that could not be translated will yield results for the actual geographical position – if you would like to query for times at an exact location, specify a radius of zero (0).

Classes/ConvertTimeRequest.html#/s:6libt.name: timeChanges
Classes/ConvertTimeRequest.html#/s:6libt.abstract: Add a list of time changes during the year to the location object. This listing e.g. shows changes caused by daylight savings time.

Classes/ConvertTimeRequest.html#/s:6libt.name: timeZoneInfo
Classes/ConvertTimeRequest.html#/s:6libt.abstract: Add time zone information under the time object.

Classes/ConvertTimeRequest.html#/s:6libt.name: verbosetime
Classes/ConvertTimeRequest.html#/s:6libt.abstract: Adds verbose time specification to all ISO 8601 time stamps.

Classes/BusinessDurationRequest.html#/s:.name: placeId
Classes/BusinessDurationRequest.html#/s:.abstract: Specify the ID of the location you would like to calculate the business duration. The ID is used to find what holidays are applicable for the given place so the calculation can exclude or include those results.

Classes/BusinessDurationRequest.html#/s:.name: country
Classes/BusinessDurationRequest.html#/s:.abstract: Specify the country for which you would like to calculate the business date.

Classes/BusinessDurationRequest.html#/s:.name: state
Classes/BusinessDurationRequest.html#/s:.abstract: Specify the state in the given country you want to calculate the business date.

Classes/BusinessDurationRequest.html#/s:.name: startDt
Classes/BusinessDurationRequest.html#/s:.abstract: Specify the ISO 8601 date for the date you want to calculate to.

Classes/BusinessDurationRequest.html#/s:.name: endDt
Classes/BusinessDurationRequest.html#/s:.abstract: Specify the ISO 8601 date for the date you want to calculate to.

Classes/BusinessDurationRequest.html#/s:.name: include
Classes/BusinessDurationRequest.html#/s:.abstract: Specify whether the result should be calculated by including instead of excluding the days specified by filter.

Classes/BusinessDurationRequest.html#/s:.name: filter
Classes/BusinessDurationRequest.html#/s:.abstract: Choose a set of types or days you want to filter on.

Classes/BusinessDurationRequest.html#/s:.name: includelAStdate
Classes/BusinessDurationRequest.html#/s:.abstract: Whether or not the last date (enddt) should be counted in the result.

Classes/BusinessDurationRequest.html#/s:.name: lang
Classes/BusinessDurationRequest.html#/s:.abstract: The preferred language for the texts. An error will be raised if the language code cannot be recognized. In case the text for a specific event cannot be retrieved in the requested language it will be returned in English instead. This is also the default language.

Classes/BusinessDurationRequest.html#/s:.name: verbosetime
Classes/BusinessDurationRequest.html#/s:.abstract: Adds verbose time specification to all ISO 8601 time stamps.

Classes/BusinessDateResponse.html#/s:6li.name: periods
Classes/BusinessDateResponse.html#/s:6li.abstract: This array will contain the calculated result for the requested period. For the XML format, it will be repeated multiple times, while for JSON, it is modeled as an array of objects with the same content.

Classes/BusinessDateRequest.html#/s:6lib.name: placeId
Classes/BusinessDateRequest.html#/s:6lib.abstract: Specify the ID of the location you would like to calculate the business date. The ID is used to find what holidays are applicable for the given place so the calculation can exclude or include those results.

Classes/BusinessDateRequest.html#/s:6lib.name: country
Classes/BusinessDateRequest.html#/s:6lib.abstract: Specify the country for which you would like to calculate the business date.

Classes/BusinessDateRequest.html#/s:6lib.name: state
Classes/BusinessDateRequest.html#/s:6lib.abstract: Specify the state in the given country you want to calculate the business date.

Classes/BusinessDateRequest.html#/s:6lib.name: startDt
Classes/BusinessDateRequest.html#/s:6lib.abstract: Specify the ISO 8601 date for the first date you are interested in.

Classes/BusinessDateRequest.html#/s:6lib.name: days
Classes/BusinessDateRequest.html#/s:6lib.abstract: Specify how many business days to count.

Classes/BusinessDateRequest.html#/s:6lib.name: include
Classes/BusinessDateRequest.html#/s:6lib.abstract: Specify whether the result should be calculated by including instead of excluding the days.

Classes/BusinessDateRequest.html#/s:6lib.name: filter
Classes/BusinessDateRequest.html#/s:6lib.abstract: Choose a set of types or days you want to filter on.

Classes/BusinessDateRequest.html#/s:6lib.name: op
Classes/BusinessDateRequest.html#/s:6lib.abstract: Set if the service should do an addition or subtraction of the specified days.

Classes/BusinessDateRequest.html#/s:6lib.name: repeatDays
Classes/BusinessDateRequest.html#/s:6lib.abstract: Set how many times the calculation should be repeated (only applicable when days parameter has exactly one number).

Classes/BusinessDateRequest.html#/s:6lib.name: lang
Classes/BusinessDateRequest.html#/s:6lib.abstract: The preferred language for the texts. An error will be raised if the language code cannot be recognized. In case the text for a specific event cannot be retrieved in the requested language it will be returned in English instead. This is also the default language.

Classes/BusinessDateRequest.html#/s:6lib.name: verbosetime
Classes/BusinessDateRequest.html#/s:6lib.abstract: Adds verbose time specification to all ISO 8601 time stamps.

Classes/AstronomyRequest.html#/s:6libtad.name: objects
Classes/AstronomyRequest.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: Specify which astronomical object you are interested in. Currently, only sun and moon are supported.

Classes/AstronomyRequest.html#/s:6libtad.name: placeId
Classes/AstronomyRequest.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: Specify the ID of the location you would like to retrieve information for. To retrieve the information for multiple places, the corresponding IDs can either be specified as a comma separated list, or by supplying the parameter multiple times (or any combination). There is a limit of maximum 10 locations per requests.

Classes/AstronomyRequest.html#/s:6libtad.name: startDate
Classes/AstronomyRequest.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: Specify the ISO 8601 date for the first date you are interested in.

Classes/AstronomyRequest.html#/s:6libtad.name: endDate
Classes/AstronomyRequest.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: The last date you are interested in. The service can be used to calculate data for a maximum of 31 days in a row. If the end date is omitted, only one day is retrieved.

Classes/AstronomyRequest.html#/s:6libtad.name: types
Classes/AstronomyRequest.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: Selection of which astronomical events you are interested in. To combine multiple classes, either separate them with commas or repeat the parameter with a different value. A negation can be expressed by prefixing the value with a tilde (~) character. Values are combined in the order they are supplied.

Classes/AstronomyRequest.html#/s:6libtad.name: geo
Classes/AstronomyRequest.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: Return longitude and latitude for the geo object.

Classes/AstronomyRequest.html#/s:6libtad.name: isoTime
Classes/AstronomyRequest.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: Adds time stamps (local time) in ISO 8601 format to all events.

Classes/AstronomyRequest.html#/s:6libtad.name: lang
Classes/AstronomyRequest.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: The preferred language for the texts. An error will be raised if the language code cannot be recognized. In case the text for a specific event cannot be retrieved in the requested language it will be returned in English instead. This is also the default language.

Classes/AstronomyRequest.html#/s:6libtad.name: radius
Classes/AstronomyRequest.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: Search radius for translating coordinates (parameter placeid) to locations. Coordinates that could not be translated will yield results for the actual geographical position – if you would like to query for times at an exact location, specify a radius of zero (0).

Classes/AstronomyRequest.html#/s:6libtad.name: utcTime
Classes/AstronomyRequest.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: Adds UTC time stamps in ISO 8601 format to all events.

Classes/AstrodataRequest.html#/s:6libtad.name: objects
Classes/AstrodataRequest.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: Specify which astronomical object you are interested in. To retrieve the information for multiple objects, the corresponding names can either be specified as a comma separated list, or by supplying the parameter multiple times (or any combination). Currently, only sun and moon are supported as objects.

Classes/AstrodataRequest.html#/s:6libtad.name: placeId
Classes/AstrodataRequest.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: Specify the ID of the location you would like to retrieve information for. To retrieve the information for multiple places, the corresponding IDs can either be specified as a comma separated list, or by supplying the parameter multiple times (or any combination). There is a limit of maximum 10 locations per requests.

Classes/AstrodataRequest.html#/s:6libtad.name: interval
Classes/AstrodataRequest.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: Specify the point(s) in time you would like to calculate data for. Multiple results can be retrieved by specifying several timestamps separated by comma, maximum 50.

Classes/AstrodataRequest.html#/s:6libtad.name: localtime
Classes/AstrodataRequest.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: Specify whether or not the intervals should be considered the local time for the place(s) or UTC time.

Classes/AstrodataRequest.html#/s:6libtad.name: isoTime
Classes/AstrodataRequest.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: Adds time stamps (local time) in ISO 8601 format to all events.

Classes/AstrodataRequest.html#/s:6libtad.name: utcTime
Classes/AstrodataRequest.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: Adds UTC time stamps in ISO 8601 format to all events.

Classes/AstrodataRequest.html#/s:6libtad.name: lang
Classes/AstrodataRequest.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: The preferred language for the texts. An error will be raised if the language code cannot be recognized. In case the text for a specific event cannot be retrieved in the requested language it will be returned in English instead. This is also the default language.

Classes/AstrodataRequest.html#/s:6libtad.name: radius
Classes/AstrodataRequest.html#/s:6libtad.abstract: Search radius for translating coordinates (parameter placeid) to locations. Coordinates that could not be translated will yield results for the actual geographical position – if you would like to query for times at an exact location, specify a radius of zero (0).
